<%- include("partials/header", { title: title }) %>

<main>
  <h2><%= category.name %></h2>

  <% if (category.name === "Recycling" || category.name === "Sustainability") { %>
    <section class="card">
      <h3>Step 1: Create a Recycled Mini Greenhouse</h3>

      <p>
        Use a clean 1-gallon clear or translucent plastic jug so sunlight can
        pass through. Carefully cut the jug almost in half around the middle,
        leaving 1 to 2 inches uncut below the handle so the top remains attached.
      </p>

      <p>
        Bend the top of the jug backward to create an opening. Cut empty toilet
        paper rolls in half and stand them upright inside the bottom of the jug.
        Fill each toilet paper roll with potting soil.
      </p>

      <h3>Step 2: Plant and Label Seeds</h3>

      <p>
        Place 1 to 2 seeds into each toilet paper roll. More than one type of
        plant can be started in the same jug because the rolls keep the plants
        separated and make them easier to transplant later.
      </p>

      <p>
        Label each plant with a popsicle stick or plant marker. Place the jug
        outside in a sunny area and water lightly each day.
      </p>

      <p>
        The jug helps protect seedlings from frost, allowing seeds to be started
        earlier in the growing season while producing stronger, hardier plants.
      </p>

      <h3>Step 3: Transplant Seedlings</h3>

      <p>
        Once the seeds have sprouted and developed several healthy leaves,
        transplant them into larger containers, planter boxes, raised beds,
        or a garden space.
      </p>

      <p>
        The toilet paper rolls help keep roots undisturbed during transplanting
        and will naturally break down in the soil over time.
      </p>

      <h3>Step 4: Make Fresh Homemade Salsa</h3>

      <p>
        After harvesting your tomatoes, jalapeños, onions, and cilantro,
        use them to make fresh homemade salsa.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a
          href="https://natashaskitchen.com/easy-homemade-salsa/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          Easy Homemade Salsa Recipe by Natasha's Kitchen
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>
  <% } %>

  <section class="project-grid">
    <% projects.forEach(project => { %>
      <article class="card">
        <a href="/project/<%= project.project_id %>">
          <h3><%= project.title %></h3>
        </a>

        <p><%= project.description %></p>

        <p>
          <strong>Date:</strong>
          <%= new Date(project.date).toLocaleDateString() %>
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Location:</strong>
          <%= project.location %>
        </p>
      </article>
    <% }) %>
  </section>

  <% if (user && user.role_name === "admin") { %>
    <p>
      <a href="/edit-category/<%= category.category_id %>">
        Edit Category
      </a>
    </p>
  <% } %>

  <p>
    <a href="/categories">Back to Categories</a>
  </p>
</main>

<%- include("partials/footer") %>